$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Egzadesimal se yon fason pou reprezante done binè nan fòm moun lizib. Li te devlope nan 19yèm syèk la pou pèmèt òdinatè yo estoke gwo kantite enfòmasyon.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Ou ka itilize egzadesimal pou konvèti ant valè desimal ak valè binè. Pou egzanp, konvèti 10011011001010 nan egzadesimal ta lakòz 0x4F. Sa vle di valè 4F reprezante nimewo binè 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Nan matematik ak syans enfòmatik, egzadesimal (tou baz 16, oswa hex) se yon sistèm nimerik pozisyon ki gen yon radiks, oswa baz, nan 16. Li itilize sèz senbòl diferan, pi souvan senbòl yo 0–9 pou reprezante valè zewo a nèf, ak A, B, C, D, E, F (oswa altènativman a–f) pou reprezante valè dis a kenz. Pa egzanp, nimewo egzadesimal 2AF3 egal, an desimal, ak (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , oswa 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Chak chif egzadesimal reprezante kat chif binè (bit) (yo rele tou yon &quot;nibble&quot;), ak itilizasyon prensipal notasyon ègzadesimal se kòm yon reprezantasyon zanmitay moun nan valè binè kode nan enfòmatik ak elektwonik dijital. Pou egzanp, valè byte yo ka varye ant 0 a 255 (dezimal) men yo ka reprezante pi fasilman kòm de chif egzadesimal nan seri 00 jiska FF. Egzadesimal tou souvan itilize pou reprezante adrès memwa òdinatè.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex se yon abrevyasyon Hexadecimal, ki baze sou yon estrikti baz -16 epi li itilize pou senplifye fason yo reprezante enstriksyon òdinatè yo. Sistèm nimewo 16 senbòl sa a te devlope kòm yon mwayen pou anpeche yon nimewo binè 8-bit, kidonk done yo ka kode nan òdinatè san efò. Li ka anprent ak tape lè l sèvi avèk de chif hex diferan ak chak chif hex demontre yon nibble oswa petèt yon fòma 4-bit.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Sistèm nimewo sa a sèvi ak 16 senbòl ki reprezante nan yon seri ant 0-9 oswa AF. 0–9 reprezante nimewo jiska nèf alòske AF reprezante pa nimerik 10–15. Kòm konpare ak twa lòt kalite sistèm nimerik yo, sistèm nimerik egzadesimal la konsidere kòm youn ki pi efikas.';
